      "rationale": "Mesh sensitivity was evaluated using two mesh densities (3.2 M and 6.8 M cells). Richardson extrapolation was not performed due to resource constraints; a third refinement level was not generated. The coarse-to-fine NIH change was 11.2%, which exceeds the 5% threshold. The team judged this acceptable given qualitative agreement trends, but the formal GCI criterion is not met. Achieved level is assessed as Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2, reflecting incomplete convergence evidence. The assessment team noted this gap but concluded overall model behavior was sufficiently understood for decision support."
